# Security patterns

## Token handling
- JWT access tokens: 15-minute expiry
- JWT refresh tokens: 7-day expiry, rotate on every use
- Refresh token reuse → invalidate entire session immediately
- Never return raw tokens in error responses
- Never log Authorization headers or token values

## Encryption
- All OAuth tokens: AES-256-GCM envelope encryption
- Unique data encryption key (DEK) per user
- Master key stored in Doppler only, never in code or .env

## Webhook verification
Always verify signatures before processing any webhook:
- Flutterwave: HMAC-SHA256 against verif-hash header
- Paystack: HMAC-SHA512 against X-Paystack-Signature header
- Return 401 immediately if signature fails — do not process

## Rate limiting
- Authenticated routes: 100 req / 15 min / user
- Unauthenticated routes: 20 req / 15 min / IP
- Auth endpoints: 5 attempts / 15 min / IP → lockout

## Forbidden patterns
- Never use Math.random() for tokens — use crypto.randomBytes()
- Never skip signature verification "just for testing"
- Never hardcode secrets — all secrets from Doppler via process.env
